can you transfer a pension and get and get a cash lump sum in the uk if you are currently contributing to a uk pension scheme it's possible you could transfer your pension to another scheme but there is no benefit in doing this unless you are changing your employer some contributory pension schemes will allow part of a pension to be taken as a lump sum on retirement but you would need to ask your fund administrator about the rules for your particular scheme if you are already a pensioner or a deferred pensioner you have ceased making contributions but have not yet retired then it is incredibly unlikely you would be able either to transfer a pension or take a cash lump sum if you are talking about a state pension then the simple answer is no Annuity Retirement plan Ponzi scheme Social security Life insurance Social Security (United States) Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation Insurance 401(k) National Insurance Tax Individual Retirement Account Department for Work and Pensions Unemployment benefit Economic Growth and Tax Relief Reconciliation Act of 2001 Trust (Law) USA Social Security debate (United States) Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Retirement Canada Health Act Taxation in the United States Employee Retirement Income Security Act Professor Mortgage Mutual fund Microeconomics Centrelink Taxation in Canada Enron Corporation Secretary of State for Work and Pensions United States Department of Veterans Affairs Meiji period Bank fraud Princely state Compensation of employees United Kingdom corporation tax Article One of the United States Constitution Student loan Citigroup Al Gore presidential campaign, 2000 Panay incident Timeline of the Enron scandal Debt Payroll Confidence trick SCO-Linux controversies Voluntary Student Unionism Income trust Economy of Russia Same-sex marriage in New York Mensal__o scandal CPU cache Dave Reichert Password Gross domestic product Money creation Robert Maxwell Public bodies and task forces of the UK governme